# Options calculator catalog sync

When working on calculators, strategies, or pricing tools, keep our catalog complete and accurate.

## Check for new calculators

Periodically compare our catalog against the reference site's calculator index:

- Reference URL (internal use only — never add this URL to app code, UI, or user-facing docs): https://projectoption.com/calculators

Workflow:

1. Fetch https://projectoption.com/calculators and list every calculator linked from that page.
2. Compare against `STRATEGIES` in `packages/options-core/src/catalog.ts`.
3. If the reference site has calculators we are missing, implement them end-to-end before considering the task done.

## Files to update when adding a calculator

| File | What to add |
|------|-------------|
| `packages/options-core/src/catalog.ts` | Strategy entry in `STRATEGIES` |
| `packages/options-core/src/strategies/index.ts` | Strategy compute function |
| `packages/options-core/src/calculator-configs.ts` | Config entry in `CALCULATOR_CONFIGS` |
| `packages/options-core/tests/strategies.test.ts` | Analytical P/L or integrity test |
| `packages/options-core/tests/calculator-configs.test.ts` | Covered automatically if config exists |
| `apps/mobile/constants/strategies.ts` | Route in `ROUTE_BY_STRATEGY` (if new id) |
| `apps/web` | Uses `@ai-options/core` catalog — no separate list needed |

## Implementation requirements for each new calculator

- Use Black-Scholes pricing from `packages/options-core/src/math/`
- Support IV and price input modes where applicable
- Return `CalculatorResult` with metrics, P/L curve, and Greeks when relevant
- Add tests that verify max profit, max loss, breakevens, or manual expiration P/L
- Match existing naming, categories, and UI patterns in web and mobile apps

## Categories (use existing ones)

- `single-leg`, `vertical`, `income`, `volatility`, `pricing`

## Before finishing any calculator work

```bash
npm test
npm run typecheck
npm run check:refs
```

Confirm `STRATEGIES.length === Object.keys(CALCULATOR_CONFIGS).length`.
